UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 226
1 number of affirmative votes shall become law.
2 (6) The veto power of the Governor shall not extend to measures enacted by the
3 people under this section.
4 (7) The General Assembly may provide by general law procedures to facilitate
5 and safeguard the initiative power of the people, but not to hamper, restrict, or impair
6 this power.
7 Section 3. This amendment shall be submitted to the voters of the
8 Commonwealth for their ratification or rejection at the time and in the manner provided
9 for under Sections 256 and 257 of the Constitution, KRS 118.415, and Sections 4 and 5
10 of this Act.
11 Section 4. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 118.415 to the contrary, the
12 Secretary of State shall cause the entirety of the question in Section 1 of this Act and the
13 entirety of the proposed amendment to the Constitution of Kentucky contained in Section
14 2 of this Act to be published at least one time in a newspaper of general circulation
15 published in this state, and shall also cause to be published at the same time and in the
16 same manner the fact that the amendment will be submitted to the voters for their
17 acceptance or rejection at the next regular election at which members of the General
18 Assembly are to be voted for. The publication required by this section and KRS 118.415
19 shall be made no later than the first Tuesday in August preceding the election at which
20 the amendment is to be voted on.
21 Section 5. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 118.415 to the contrary, the
22 Secretary of State, not later than the second Monday after the second Tuesday in August
23 preceding the next regular election at which members of the General Assembly are to be
24 chosen in a year in which there is not an election for President and Vice President of the
25 United States, or not later than the Thursday after the first Tuesday in September
26 preceding a regular election in a year in which there is an election for President and Vice
27 President of the United States, shall certify the entirety of the question in Section 1 of this
